"{\"uid\": \"wrkf.org-show-louisiana-considered-2024-08-21-lsus-vernon-norwood-reflects-on-journey-after-winning-gold-at-olympics-louisianas-higher-ed-gender-pay-gap\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  This newscast is updated weekdays at 6am, 9am, noon, 3pm, and 6pm.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 68, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to recent researchby the Louisiana Illuminator, there is a persistent pay gap between men and women at the state's public institutions of higher education.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"score\": 0.9999890040682856, \"rank\": 1.0996033260096962e-05, \"text\": \"Louisiana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Illuminator reviewed salaries of more than 7,700 full-time or equivalent instructional faculty at the public colleges and universities in Louisiana.\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 378, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"score\": 0.9999890040682856, \"rank\": 1.0996033260096962e-05, \"text\": \"Louisiana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ReporterPiper Hutchinsonhelps break down the study and explains some potential causes of the pay disparity.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Paris Olympics saw no shortage of impressive feats from Louisiana athletes.Of the nearly 30 competitorswho went to or currently attend LSU, eight came home with medals.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"score\": 0.9999890040682856, \"rank\": 1.0996033260096962e-05, \"text\": \"Louisiana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana\"}, {\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana_State_University\", \"score\": 0.8623447324543605, \"rank\": 0.12221287230148481, \"text\": \"LSU\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana_State_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louisiana_State_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track athleteVernon Norwoodcame home with two, a silver in the mixed 4 x 400 relay and a gold in the men's 4 x 400 relay - for which he was also a defending champion.\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Norwood joins us for more on his incredible performance on the track and unexpected journey to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.9975043046926224, \"rank\": 0.002501939384813967, \"text\": \"Norwood\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwood_Football_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"-  Today's episode of Louisiana Considered was hosted by Adam Vos.\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our managing producer is Alana Schreiber; our contributing producers are Matt Bloom and Adam Vos; we receive production and technical support from Garrett Pittman and our assistant producer, Aubry Procell.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuart_Schreiber\", \"score\": 0.9999998979903973, \"rank\": 1.0200953753443254e-07, \"text\": \"Schreiber\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stuart_